Title: '&quot;Out of Office&quot;: the young professional in Portugal'
DateModified: '2019-02-14'
DatePublished: '2019-02-14'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/out-of-office-the-young-professional-in-portugal
SetInCountry: South Africa
Category: A leap into the unknown
AuthorName: Gabriela  Carolus
AuthorCountry: South Africa
Text: "Gabriela Carolus is a South African teaching ESL in South Korea. She is a novice\
  \ poet and blogger. She writes about aspects of life that millennials face in their\
  \ daily interactions with all generations. In her writing, Gabriela explores boundaries\
  \ between politics, religion, faith, music, science, sexuality and love. Poetry\
  \ has been her hobby for many years. She has recently compiled a collection of poems\
  \ of her journey after retrenchment and life as a millennial in the new economic\
  \ state. \n\nFor this travel article, the writer will capture the \"City\" girls\
  \ \"out of office\" experience in Portugal. Moreover, she will focus on the journey\
  \ from leaving the Cape Town, CBD for Portugal.  The aim of the piece is to capture\
  \ travels from departure, adjusting from the rush to enjoying the \"peace of mind\"\
  \ in Portugal's hiking experiences. The main themes are 1) costs and benefits of\
  \ leaving the office for Portugal, 2) the outdoor activities for women , and 3)\
  \ reintegrating from the office to the outdoor. The author will then close will\
  \ a focus on outdoor experiences for women in Portugal. Reference will include links\
  \ from travel agents in Portugal with a focus on women , the corporate to the young\
  \ professional package and lastly safety measures for solo travelers in Portugal."
